        "title": "Java Date Comparison",
        "body": "<p>According to Java API <code>public boolean before(Date when)<\/code><\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>true if and only if the instant of time represented by this Date\n  object is strictly earlier than the instant represented by when; false\n  otherwise.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Now I have to check if date input by user is greater than current date then only it will accept the input otherwise throw exception so i tried below <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if(userInputDate.before(new Date())){\n      throw new Exception(\"Some Message\");\n     }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But if both date are same then also it going to inside <code>if<\/code> statement .Do it mean it will calculate time and then check rather than comparing date? If yes how to resolve my issue ?<\/p>\n\n<p>Can any one tell me how to add check for this?<\/p>\n",
